      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): forward temperature and top_p through OpenAI-compatible HTTP APIs",
        "body": "Both `/v1/chat/completions` and `/v1/responses` accept `temperature` and `top_p` in the request body, but the values never reached the upstream provider:\n\n- `openai-http` did not parse them.\n- `openresponses-http` schema accepted them as \"Phase 1: ignore but accept\"; the handler read only `max_output_tokens`.\n- `createStreamFnWithExtraParams` forwarded only temperature/maxTokens to the underlying stream function, so even a newly added `AgentStreamParams.topP` would have been silently dropped mid-flight.\n\nExtend `AgentStreamParams` with `topP`, thread it through the runtime stream wrapper, and write `top_p` in both the OpenAI Responses and Chat Completions builders. Add `top_p` to `OPENAI_CODEX_RESPONSES_UNSUPPORTED_PARAMS` so the ChatGPT-based Codex Responses backend strips it server-side, matching how temperature is already handled.\n\nFixes #81274. Refs #65345.",
